Iceland drew a lot of interest among things from Expedia.com like Iceland tours to Iceland-flight.com. Iceland’s tourism office also said they’ve posted a travel advice for travelers to check out. For travelers to Iceland, according to the Iceland Tourism Office, “A circular drive to the world famous secret lagoon takes us along a route showing geothermal fields and across lava plains and we clearly see the influence of the river Hvita coming down from the South Iceland volcano areas. The Secret lagoon will certainly open your eyes to geothermal activity and you will never be sceptical of a hot bath again. After the bath we relax and enjoy refreshments in geothermal greenhouses nearby. We then drive past preserving glaciers and indentically similar looking lava fields.”
